{{wikipedia}}
==English==
===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ˈkʌmpækt/ or /kəmˈpækt/ (''Canadian'')
===Etymology===
From Latin ''compactus'' from [[Ancient Greek]] [[συμπακτός]] (''sympaktοs'') "well joined together, well connected together", from prefix [[σύν-]] , [[σύμ-]] (''syn- , sym-'') "with, together" + [[πακτός]] (''paktos'') the [[Doric]] form of the [[Ionic]] [[πηκτός]] (''pektos'') "well joined, well fitted".

===Adjective===
'''compact'''
#Closely packed together.
#Having all necessary features fit neatly in a small space.
#{{topology}} Closed and bounded; having a finite [[subcover]] for every open cover.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[tiivis]] (1), [[kompakti]] (2)
*Greek: [[συμπακτός]] (''sympaktos'') {{m}}

====Derived terms====
*[[compact disc]]
*[[compact car]]

===Noun===
'''compact'''  (''plural:'' '''compacts''')
#A small mirror and powder combination folding item which fits into a woman's purse.
#An agreement or contract (from latin ''compactum'')

===Verb===
'''to compact''' ([[compacted]], [[compacting]])
#Make more dense; compress.

